<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100620963090029></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100620963090029><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=43308&mid=100620963090029>Play Style</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=43308&mid=100620963090029#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91598><span id= >Shallinar</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>28 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 19th 5:40 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.94]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am left handed in real life. This has given me a great advantage in key-board usage. I have set the spells keys to the number pad, sit/stand as the 0 key on the number pad as well, center view as the number pad + key instead of the number pad 5 key and target self/pet as the * key on the number pad. <br><br>This allows me to use the user defined hot keys for other purposes. An assist key is imperative at mid to high levels to help with slowing or debuffing. I have also programmed a macro to let me enter my spell book as I use the panoramic view mode. A corpse hot key is also highly useful as I tend to either die alot or survive and have to drag party members if we were annihilated.<br><br>This can also be set up for right handed individuals but using the opposite side of the keyboard but isn't quite so easy since some of these keys are already in use for other functions. They will need to be redifined.<br><br>To change these settings go into options &gt; keyboard and move through the pages until you see the functions you want to define.<br>&nbsp;<br>Shallinar Icefyre<br>Enchanter of Veeshan</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
